From 3e3e756f60c77bed8c46aa6ace6ef77dea3012d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 15:20:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] HPIR: header-path query resolution as shared IR for
 split-store table-RAG

Main contribution: a single query-understanding module that maps an NL table
question to a hierarchical header-path intent, applied in two regimes to attack
both measured bottlenecks (retrieval 29% / answer 71%) whose common cause is
that the query's target header path is never made explicit.

- rag_agent/query/header_path_resolver.py
  * expand_for_retrieval (corpus-free): strip narrative, keep header-likely
    tokens + operation hints; keep year tokens (HiTab year columns)
  * resolve_against_table (table-grounded): rank the table's real top/left
    header paths against the query; every binding is guaranteed to exist
  * resolve_intent: optional LLM refinement intersected with the real header
    inventory + deterministic backfill, so no hallucinated binding can leak
- scripts/hpir_retrieval_eval.py: raw vs HPIR-expanded query on the same pool
  (dense / keyword), paired bootstrap 95% CI + exact McNemar on R@1, per-class
- scripts/method_grounded.py: add --mode hpir (naive/grounded/hpir 3-way
  ablation), injecting resolved header-path bindings into the grounded prompt
- tests/test_header_path_resolver.py: 11 deterministic tests (no data/GPU),
  full suite 30 passing
- stores/vector_store.py: lazy chromadb import so the package imports in a bare
  env (enables CI/unit tests without chroma)
- docs/METHOD_HPIR.md, configs/hpir.yaml, STATE.md progress log

Numbers to be produced on the data/GPU machine (this container has no HiTab
data, GPU, Qwen, or Chroma); harness + unit tests are complete here.

https://claude.ai/code/session_017qWt67PrHGBEDxRQwzXo4W
